h3. Summary
Loading a *Service Desk Request* through the *Customer Portal* fails with a NullPointerException, which is displayed as an XML file:
 [^500error.xml] 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a project;
# Create an issue in this project;
# Grant *Anonymous* access and permission to comment on this project;
# As an anonymous user, add a comment to this ticket.
# Install *JIRA Service Desk*;
# Create a Service Desk from this project;
# Try to access this issue from the *Customer Portal*.

h3. Expected Results
The customer would be able to access the issue with no problem.


h3. Actual Results
The user is unable to open the request, and an XML file is displayed instead: [^500error.xml]
The following is displayed in the {{atlassian-jira.log}} file and the complete stack trace can be found in  [^complete_stack_trace.txt] .
{code}
Failed to get event initiating user to set issue property 'request.public-activity.lastupdated'
{code}
 !error.png|thumbnail!  

h3. Workaround
* Upgrade to *JIRA Service Desk 2.3.5+*.
* Or delete the offending comment and re-add it as a JIRA user.

