h3. {color:#3572b0}Summary{color}
When inviting a customer/sending an invitation email through *JIRA Service Desk*, the invitation uses the inviter current URL instead of using the Base URL, causing problems if the inviter is using localhost, for example.

h3. {color:#3572b0}Steps to Reproduce{color}
# Install latest JIRA and JIRA Service Desk;
# Configure the *Base URL* in the *Administration » General Configuration* page to e.g. "{{my.jira.com}}";
# Access JIRA using localhost or a different URL that is different from JIRA's Base URL.
# Configure an *outgoing mail* for JIRA;
# Create a new *Service Desk*;
# Navigate to *Service Desk » "My First Service Desk" » People » Customers*;
# Click *Invite customers* and send an invitation to an email.

h3. {color:#3572b0}Expected Results{color}
The *Visit Portal* button would send the invitee to the JIRA *Base URL*.

h3. {color:#3572b0}Actual Results{color}
The invitee is sent to the URL the inviter was accessing *JIRA Service Desk* from.

h3.{color:#3572b0}Workaround{color}
Send invites when accessing JIRA through the Base URL.

